Essential.1: Date where the sample used in the WSI was sampled
Essential.2: Source of the tissue sample (e.g., biopsy, surgical specimen).
Essential.3: Location of the tumor in the body
Essential.4: Pathological tumor stage at the time of diagnosis.
Essential.5: Pathological nodal stage at the time of diagnosis.
Essential.6: Pathological metastasis stage at the time of diagnosis.
Essential.8: Histological caracterization made by the pathologist
Low Priority.1: Human Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor-2 (HER2) status
Low Priority.2: The patient received a treatment before primary cancer treatment (such as surgery)
